Data Collector Network Guide
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
Click "Data-Collector" within the main menu.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
Select "Network".
4
Enter an IP address on the same network as the connected device in the "IP
Address/Subnet Mask" field. The IP address format is "IP/Subnet Mask". If you
want to set multiple IP addresses, remember to separate them with a comma ','.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
5
You can set a dynamic connection by selecting "DHCP". The "IP Address" field
won't be taken into account when using DHCP.
6
Move to "Static Routes".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
7
Click on the "+" icon to add a new static route. You can also edit an existing route,
by clicking on the "pencil" icon, or delete one by clicking on the "red trash" icon.
8
When you click on the "+" icon to add a new route, a "Add new line" tab appears.
Enter the "Subnetwork/Subnet Mask". Note: 10.1.4.1 is written as 10.1.4.1/24.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 5
9
Insert the Gateway IP address without Subnet Mask inside the "Gateway" field
10
Click the "Ok" button to add the new static route to the table.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 6
11
Move to "NTP".
12
Into "NTP synchronization settings" you can select "Use custom NTP server"
checkbox to use a custom NTP Server into Data Collector network. On the other
hand, you can use the default one, "User Data sender signal", in which the Data
Sender updates the time of the Data Collector every 15 minutes.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 7
13
If you select "Use custom NTP server" , you can enter one or several custom IP
addresses in the new "NTP Server address" field. If you want more than one IP
address separating them with a comma ",". Example: 192.1.1.0, 10.50.0.0, ...
If for some reason you wish to disable all NTP synchronizations, select "Use
custom NTP server" and leave the "NTP server address" text box blank.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 8
14
If you click "Synchronise" button when the "Data Sender signal" is active, the
system will attempt to synchronize the time by taking it from the Data Sender.
Instead, if "Custom NTP server" is active, the time will be synchronized via the
machine's network, based on the IP you have entered in the text box.
15
You can now click the "Save" button.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 9
16
Click the "Apply" button to apply the new configurations.
